South African superstar comedian Trevor Noah is looking to keep the jokes coming this festive season. The ever hard working Noah has no intentions of slowing down for the upcoming holiday season as he has announced a brand new comedy special. The Daily Show host’s new stand up special titled Son of Patricia, will hit Netflix as early as next month, still, his fans can hardly wait. Son of Patricia will touch on “racism, immigration, camping and more,” according to Netflix. This will be the 34 year-old’s second special with the streaming service following his hugely successful Afraid of the Dark which premiered in 2017. Son of Patricia will debut on Netflix onTuesday, November 20. My new standup special “Son Of Patricia” premieres Nov 20th on @NetflixIsAJoke! #TrevorNoah #SonOfPatricia #Netflix A post shared by  Trevor Noah (@trevornoah) on Oct 22, 2018 at 6:01am PDT   